registers.name: TASKS_START
registers.description: Starts continuous I2S transfer. Also starts MCK generator when this is enabled.

registers.name: TASKS_STOP
registers.description: Stops I2S transfer. Also stops MCK generator. Triggering this task will cause the {event:STOPPED} event to be generated.

registers.name: EVENTS_RXPTRUPD
registers.description: The RXD.PTR register has been copied to internal double-buffers. When the I2S module is started and RX is enabled, this event will be generated for every RXTXD.MAXCNT words that are received on the SDIN pin.

registers.name: EVENTS_TXPTRUPD
registers.description: The TDX.PTR register has been copied to internal double-buffers. When the I2S module is started and TX is enabled, this event will be generated for every RXTXD.MAXCNT words that are sent on the SDOUT pin.

registers.name: TASKS_ACTIVATE
registers.description: Activate NFC peripheral for incoming and outgoing frames, change state to activated

registers.name: TASKS_SENSE
registers.description: Enable NFC sense field mode, change state to sense mode

registers.name: TASKS_STARTTX
registers.description: Start transmission of a outgoing frame, change state to transmit

registers.name: TASKS_GOIDLE
registers.description: Force state machine to IDLE state

registers.name: TASKS_GOSLEEP
registers.description: Force state machine to SLEEP_A state

registers.name: EVENTS_READY
registers.description: The NFC peripheral is ready to receive and send frames

registers.name: EVENTS_TXFRAMESTART
registers.description: Marks the start of the first symbol of a transmitted frame

registers.name: EVENTS_TXFRAMEEND
registers.description: Marks the end of the last transmitted on-air symbol of a frame

registers.name: EVENTS_RXFRAMESTART
registers.description: Marks the end of the first symbol of a received frame

registers.name: EVENTS_RXFRAMEEND
registers.description: Received data have been checked (CRC, parity) and transferred to RAM, and EasyDMA has ended accessing the RX buffer

registers.name: EVENTS_ERROR
registers.description: NFC error reported. The ERRORSTATUS register contains details on the source of the error.

registers.name: EVENTS_RXERROR
registers.description: NFC RX frame error reported. The FRAMESTATUS.RX register contains details on the source of the error.

registers.name: EVENTS_ENDRX
registers.description: RX buffer (as defined by PACKETPTR and MAXLEN) in Data RAM full.

registers.name: EVENTS_ENDTX
registers.description: Transmission of data in RAM has ended, and EasyDMA has ended accessing the TX buffer

registers.name: EVENTS_AUTOCOLRESSTARTED
registers.description: Auto collision resolution process has started

registers.name: EVENTS_COLLISION
registers.description: NFC Auto collision resolution error reported.

registers.name: EVENTS_SELECTED
registers.description: NFC Auto collision resolution successfully completed

registers.name: EVENTS_STARTED
registers.description: EasyDMA is ready to receive or send frames.
